data.content:
Your code **does not use `Thread.Abort`**, `Thread.Interrupt`, or catch `ThreadAbortException`. It only uses `Thread.Start`, `Thread.Join`, and `Thread.Sleep` — all of which work identically on .NET 8.

**No Thread.Abort migration is needed here.**

That said, for a .NET 8 modernization, consider replacing the manual `Thread` usage with `Task.WhenAll` + `Parallel.ForEachAsync`, which is simpler and more efficient:

```csharp
public async Task RunBatchAsync(List<WorkItem> items)
{
    await Parallel.ForEachAsync(items, async (item, ct) =>
    {
        await Task.Run(() => Process(item), ct);
    });
}
```

